      "module_path": "signal",
      "docs": "Secondary port for the argless signal orchestrator functions (CN-16 / CN-17 / D8). Provides active-track ID (`active_track_id()`), TDDD-enabled layer list (`enabled_layers(track_id)`), and per-layer catalogue file bytes (`catalogue_bytes(track_id, layer)`). The usecase orchestrator calls `active_track_id()` first, then passes the resolved `TrackId` explicitly to `enabled_layers` and `catalogue_bytes` — making active-track resolution a usecase responsibility. The port does NOT return file paths — per D8-4, signals-file path construction is an infrastructure responsibility (infrastructure primitives construct the output path from the layer ID). The usecase function receives bytes from this port, computes SHA-256 hex, and passes `(LayerId, sha256_hex)` to the `per_layer_fn` closure. Declared in `libs/usecase/src/signal/`; implemented by a local filesystem adapter in `libs/infrastructure/src/`. `apps/cli-composition/src/signal.rs` only wires that adapter and the `per_layer_fn` closures into the usecase orchestrator.",
      "spec_refs": [
